sentences: In 1985 the choir was signed by Portrait Records, a sister label of CBS Records, and they persuaded the choir to shorten the choir's name to The Inspirational Choir.
In 1989 the choir recorded a live album, A Charge To Keep, although it wasn't until nearly two years later that it was released.
A Charge To Keep (Opal Records, June 1991)
"I've Got a Feeling" b/w "Right There" (Portrait, Sept 1985)
By the early 1990s Francis had moved on and founded the Ruach Ministries.
The choir was founded in the early 1980s by John Francis, who also the co-founded of the London Community Gospel Choir.
Francis was brought up in the church and his father was the pastor of a church in Islington, London.
In 1989 the choir recorded a live album, A Charge To Keep, although it wasn't until nearly two years later that it was released.
"Pick Me Up" b/w "Do Not Pass Me By" (Stiff, Nov 1983)
"Abide with Me" b/w "Sweet Holy Spirit" (Portrait, Dec 1984) Reached No. 36 in the UK Singles Chart
"One Love (People Get Ready)" b/w "Right There" (Portrait, Feb 1986)
"(Your Love Has Lifted Me) Higher and Higher" b/w "Amazing Grace" (Portrait, Nov 1986)
